							<p>A 2D game made in <a href="https://unity3d.com/">Unity3d</a>... Not quite as conflicting as it sounds. It's a simple
								puzzle game <span style="text-decoration: line-through;">based</span> ported from the
								original flash game, <a href="http://jayisgames.com/games/spybot-the-nightfall-incident/">The Nightfall Incident</a> (shown in above picture).
								It's not quite <i>The Matrix Reloaded</i> to <i>The Matrix</i> (or in other words, it's not a sequel);
								probably somewhere between an HD remake/remaster (without actually making assets HD?!) and a port.
							</p>
							<p>
								I'm using <a href="https://github.com/SacredSkull/the-nightfall-recurrence/tree/develop/Assets/Resources/Sprites">all of the visual assets from the original game</a> but I'll probably end up
								recreating them eventually as I want to add new enemies and tools, so will need to make those anyway.
							</p>
							<p>
								Rather than design my own level storage format or editing tools, I opted for
								<a href="https://github.com/bjorn/tiled">Tiled</a>. The plan is to allow users to create
								and submit levels to a repository, so using a popular and mature solution is a good idea.
							</p>
